cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NA. 

This paper deals with computational topology and algorithms for constructing simplicial complexes from point clouds. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves geometric computations and optimization, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely category. The use of topological data analysis and machine learning techniques implies cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible categories. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for constructing the epsilon-net landmarks, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, indicating cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category.
